data.title: 2023.134.002 - Campbell, Gayle D.
data.text: Description Black & white photograph measuring 6" x 4" and depicting an elevated view of the skyline of downtown Tulsa, OK, circa 1930. The view looks southwest. The center of the photograph shows the Medical and Dental Arts Building, located at 108 West 6th Street. Holy Family Cathedral is visible at the far left, located at 810 South Boulder Avenue. The Arkansas River, 11th Street Bridge, and the refinery of the Mid-Continent Petroleum Corporation are visible in the background.
